isExactlyCoveringCell(EditorCell) - Method in class jetbrains.mps.nodeEditor.selection.EditorCellSelection
This method returns true if current selection exactly covers a given cell There are three possibilities: 1) selected cell is a child of a given cell 2) selected cell is a parent of a given cell 3) selected cell is in a different tree than the given cell Analysis: Let's call the given cell "terminal cell" 1) in this case, we can say that the selected cell covers the given cell if none of the cells on the materialized path from selected cell to terminal cell has any siblings.
